01:55:58.952 --> 01:56:01.512
And I don't give a shit.

01:56:01.587 --> 01:56:07.082
Perhaps it's time to remind you this is
not simply a dispute with a putative suitor.

01:56:07.160 --> 01:56:11.096
This is me.
So be careful, Bill.

01:56:11.164 --> 01:56:14.691
Cut all that "Bill" crap
out, you son of a bitch.

01:56:14.767 --> 01:56:18.999
I'll say it again.
Be careful, Bill.

01:56:27.213 --> 01:56:30.842
Can I help you? Excuse
me, can I help you?

01:56:30.917 --> 01:56:35.217
Yes. Dr. Parrish,
please.

01:56:35.288 --> 01:56:38.587
<i>She comes on at 6:00.</i>

01:56:38.658 --> 01:56:40.592
Oh.

01:56:49.936 --> 01:56:51.927
Hi.

01:56:54.507 --> 01:56:57.999
<i>Where's Joe?
Joe?</i>

01:56:59.946 --> 01:57:02.676
Joe's not around.

01:57:03.883 --> 01:57:07.478
<i>Do you know where he is? I don't know.</i>

01:57:07.553 --> 01:57:09.544
Oh.

01:57:10.890 --> 01:57:13.723
Why are you
looking for Joe?

01:57:13.793 --> 01:57:17.786
<i>Love. Passion.
Obsession.</i>

01:57:17.864 --> 01:57:21.061
All those things
you told me to wait for.

01:57:21.134 --> 01:57:23.602
They've arrived.
This is crazy.

01:57:26.406 --> 01:57:28.271
Why?

01:57:28.341 --> 01:57:31.469
A man shows up, almost
never leaves your side.

01:57:31.544 --> 01:57:36.140
Well, you clearly trust him,
depend on him.

01:57:36.215 --> 01:57:39.981
So why aren't those things
good enough for me?

01:57:40.053 --> 01:57:42.920
<i>You don't know anything about
Joe. What are you afraid of?</i>

01:57:42.989 --> 01:57:46.550
That I'll fall
head over heels for Joe?

01:57:47.794 --> 01:57:50.854
Well, I have. Just
like you did with Mom.

01:57:50.930 --> 01:57:54.058
Isn't that what you've
always wanted for me?

01:57:54.133 --> 01:57:56.067
Susan...

01:57:58.438 --> 01:58:02.431
I don't think Joe is
gonna be with us long.

01:58:02.508 --> 01:58:05.306
Where is he going?

01:58:05.378 --> 01:58:07.778
I don't know.

01:58:07.847 --> 01:58:10.782
<i>I can't say.
Oh, come on.</i>

01:58:10.850 --> 01:58:15.583
The guy's working with you. You know chapter
and verse about everyone working with you.

01:58:15.655 --> 01:58:18.647
<i>In this case I can't. I...</i>

01:58:18.724 --> 01:58:24.253
I only will tell you that with Joe,
you're on... very, very dangerous ground.

01:58:32.171 --> 01:58:34.139
I love him.

01:58:34.207 --> 01:58:38.507
I don't care if you love
him! I'm telling you!

01:58:49.322 --> 01:58:52.086
Joe's no good for you.

01:58:54.227 --> 01:58:57.321
Of course not, Daddy.

01:58:57.396 --> 01:58:59.330
I'm sorry.

01:59:04.070 --> 01:59:06.834
I love you too.

01:59:37.003 --> 01:59:41.667
Mr. Bad News.
'Bout time you show up.

01:59:45.745 --> 01:59:48.646
Don't be feisty, sister.

01:59:48.714 --> 01:59:51.114
I'm not feisty,
mister.

01:59:51.184 --> 01:59:54.711
You come for me?
That's good news.

01:59:56.589 --> 01:59:59.353
No, I come
to see the doctor.

01:59:59.425 --> 02:00:02.258
Doctor?
Mm-hmm.

02:00:02.328 --> 02:00:05.456
What could be wrong with you? Nothin'.

02:00:07.400 --> 02:00:11.359
Ohh. You come
to see doctor lady?

02:00:11.437 --> 02:00:13.905
Yeah, man.
My doctor lady?

02:00:15.942 --> 02:00:18.433
Mine too, you know.

02:00:20.513 --> 02:00:23.573
You're in love?

02:00:30.089 --> 02:00:33.058
You're loved back?

02:00:39.932 --> 02:00:43.732
She know your real self?

02:00:43.803 --> 02:00:47.136
- She know how she feel.
- Backside!

02:00:47.206 --> 02:00:49.902
What the hell kind
of business this is.

02:00:49.976 --> 02:00:52.410
Don't need you okayin'.

02:00:52.478 --> 02:00:56.915
<i>Schoolboy things in your
head. Badness for you.</i>

02:00:56.983 --> 02:00:59.349
Badness for her.

02:00:59.418 --> 02:01:02.717
Badness for me,
lyin' here,

02:01:02.788 --> 02:01:04.915
tumor big as a breadfruit,

02:01:04.991 --> 02:01:09.621
poisonin' me inside,
and waitin'.

02:01:09.695 --> 02:01:13.324
Bring you flowers, and all
I's gettin' is aggravation.

02:01:13.399 --> 02:01:16.596
The only flowers
I want to see...

02:01:16.669 --> 02:01:21.402
is the ones over my peaceful
self resting in the dirt.

02:01:21.474 --> 02:01:24.739
Can't do no right by people. Come
to take you, you want to stay.

02:01:24.810 --> 02:01:28.143
Leave you stay, you want to go. Rahtid.

02:01:30.883 --> 02:01:35.513
You're not in
your right place, mister.

02:01:35.588 --> 02:01:37.988
Me neither.

02:01:38.057 --> 02:01:40.048
No more.

02:01:40.126 --> 02:01:42.959
Take me, and you come
with me now.

02:01:53.906 --> 02:01:57.034
But I not lonely here.

02:01:59.211 --> 02:02:02.009
Somebody want me here.

02:02:03.849 --> 02:02:05.976
Hmm.

02:02:06.052 --> 02:02:09.818
It nice
it happen to you.

02:02:09.889 --> 02:02:13.655
Like you come to the island
and had a holiday.

02:02:15.594 --> 02:02:20.190
Sun didn't burn you red-red,
just brown.

02:02:20.266 --> 02:02:25.260
<i>You sleep,
and no mosquito eat you.</i>

02:02:25.338 --> 02:02:29.638
But the truth is,
it bound to happen...

02:02:29.709 --> 02:02:32.542
if you stay long enough.

02:02:34.280 --> 02:02:38.910
So take that nice picture you
got in your head home with you,

02:02:40.386 --> 02:02:43.514
but don't be fooled.

02:02:47.660 --> 02:02:50.959
We lonely here mostly too.

02:02:52.832 --> 02:02:55.767
<i>If we lucky, maybe...</i>

02:02:57.370 --> 02:03:01.466
we got some nice pictures
to take with us.

02:03:25.598 --> 02:03:28.499
You got
enough nice pictures?

02:03:32.738 --> 02:03:34.672
Yes.

02:04:29.195 --> 02:04:31.789
Good-bye, sister.

02:04:55.354 --> 02:04:57.845
Yes?

02:04:57.923 --> 02:05:01.791
I have the feeling,
all in all,

02:05:01.861 --> 02:05:06.560
what I made this voyage for
has served its purpose.

02:05:09.101 --> 02:05:13.265
What are you saying?
It's time to go?

02:05:20.145 --> 02:05:22.477
I'm ready.

02:05:22.548 --> 02:05:24.914
You are?

02:05:26.352 --> 02:05:28.445
Yeah.

02:05:30.990 --> 02:05:36.121
Good. Tomorrow.
After the party.

02:06:07.026 --> 02:06:09.119
Yes, Helen?
Telephone call, sir.

02:06:09.194 --> 02:06:11.856
Mr. Sloane from New York. Thank you.

02:06:11.931 --> 02:06:13.865
Excuse me.

02:06:24.743 --> 02:06:26.802
Thank you.

02:06:30.950 --> 02:06:32.884
Hey!

02:06:33.953 --> 02:06:35.887
Hey.

02:06:38.057 --> 02:06:40.525
Red or white?

02:06:40.593 --> 02:06:43.027
No. No, thank you.
Have a drink.

02:06:43.095 --> 02:06:46.496
You look like you need
one as bad as me. I do?

02:06:50.269 --> 02:06:53.636
Quince?
Mm-hmm.

02:06:53.706 --> 02:06:56.334
I find myself
a little confused.

02:07:00.112 --> 02:07:02.546
Confused, huh?
Yes.

02:07:02.615 --> 02:07:04.606
About what?
Love.

02:07:04.683 --> 02:07:07.311
Love.

02:07:07.386 --> 02:07:11.049
Oh, man.
I got problems of my own.

02:07:14.293 --> 02:07:18.354
You love Allison, don't you? Yes, I do.

02:07:18.430 --> 02:07:20.364
How did you meet?

02:07:21.867 --> 02:07:24.233
Well, um,

02:07:24.303 --> 02:07:28.399
I was this world-class loser, and
she was this happy little rich girl,

02:07:28.474 --> 02:07:31.671
and for some reason
she took me in.

02:07:33.579 --> 02:07:36.309
But Allison loves you.

02:07:46.992 --> 02:07:49.324
How do you know?

02:07:54.400 --> 02:07:58.166
Because she knows the worst
thing about me, and it's okay.

02:07:58.237 --> 02:08:02.537
What is it? No, it's not one
thing. It's just an idea, Joe.

02:08:02.608 --> 02:08:05.509
It's just, um, um...

02:08:07.012 --> 02:08:11.244
It's like you know
each other's secrets,

02:08:12.351 --> 02:08:16.344
your deepest,
darkest secrets.

02:08:16.422 --> 02:08:21.291
Deepest, darkest secrets? Yeah,
and then you... you're free.

02:08:21.360 --> 02:08:23.351
Free?

02:08:24.530 --> 02:08:27.499
You're free!
You're free to l...

02:08:27.566 --> 02:08:30.194
love each other
completely, totally.

02:08:30.269 --> 02:08:33.830
Just no fear.

02:08:33.906 --> 02:08:37.637
So there's nothing you don't know
about each other, and it's okay.

02:08:40.379 --> 02:08:42.313
Hmm.

02:08:51.090 --> 02:08:56.995
Do you like me, Joe? Oh, yes,
Quince. You're one of my favorites.

02:09:02.034 --> 02:09:07.370
What would you say if you knew it
was me who brought down Bill Parrish?

02:09:10.609 --> 02:09:14.602
Oh, I told Drew and the board
that Bill depended on you.

02:09:14.680 --> 02:09:17.478
Drew and Bontecou are gonna chop up
the company, sell it off for parts.

02:09:17.549 --> 02:09:19.483
Bontecou was outside.
Drew was Mr. Inside.

02:09:19.551 --> 02:09:24.614
And I was the fool
who made it all happen.

02:09:27.726 --> 02:09:29.694
Ohh...

02:09:30.763 --> 02:09:32.697
God.

02:09:40.272 --> 02:09:42.797
What do I do?

02:09:42.875 --> 02:09:46.003
Go to Bill Parrish
and tell him the truth.

02:09:46.078 --> 02:09:48.512
He'll forgive you.

02:09:50.716 --> 02:09:53.776
You think so?
Yes.

02:09:56.722 --> 02:09:59.782
You think I should wait
till after the party?

02:09:59.858 --> 02:10:01.792
No.

02:10:04.797 --> 02:10:07.197
No.

02:10:07.266 --> 02:10:10.861
Four down here
and a sturgeon up there.

02:10:10.936 --> 02:10:13.734
<i>This one is perfect.
Absolutely.</i>

02:10:13.806 --> 02:10:17.435
<i>Okay, I think I want
four here like that...</i>

02:10:17.509 --> 02:10:19.977
Hi, Daddy.
Hi.

02:10:20.045 --> 02:10:22.673
What do you think?

02:10:22.748 --> 02:10:26.377
Well, it's, uh...
it's starting to grow on me.

02:10:26.451 --> 02:10:29.716
Oh, I've got a baritone
with a balalaika...

02:10:29.788 --> 02:10:32.382
coming from
the Russian Tea Room.

02:10:32.457 --> 02:10:36.553
I've dressed him in a Cossack shirt,
and he'll be singing Nelson Eddy songs.

02:10:36.628 --> 02:10:38.562
Wow.

02:10:40.465 --> 02:10:42.831
You really are amazing.

02:10:42.901 --> 02:10:47.201
But why, oh, why, Allison,
are you doing all this?

02:10:50.776 --> 02:10:55.440
I do it because I love
you. Everybody loves you:

02:10:55.514 --> 02:10:59.746
Mommy, wherever she is,
Susan, Quince...

02:11:01.119 --> 02:11:05.579
<i>all the people you work with,
anyone who's ever met you.</i>

02:11:06.792 --> 02:11:09.056
Ohh, Daddy.

02:11:09.127 --> 02:11:13.257
After all, you've been
a wonderful father.

02:11:15.534 --> 02:11:17.934
Yeah, well,

02:11:18.003 --> 02:11:20.164
I haven't been the father
to you that, uh...

02:11:20.239 --> 02:11:22.935
That you've been to Susan?
I wasn't going to say that.

02:11:23.008 --> 02:11:26.808
But that's what you were
thinking. And that's okay.

02:11:26.879 --> 02:11:29.074
Because I know
that you love me.

02:11:29.147 --> 02:11:32.412
I mean, it's not
like it is with her.

02:11:32.484 --> 02:11:36.215
Whenever she walks into the
room, your eyes light up.

02:11:36.288 --> 02:11:39.553
She always gets a smile
from you, as opposed to me.

02:11:39.625 --> 02:11:42.458
When I walk in,

02:11:42.527 --> 02:11:46.554
this look comes over your face,
like, "What does she want now?"

02:11:46.632 --> 02:11:50.329
<i>But you've never let either
of us want for anything.</i>

02:11:50.402 --> 02:11:54.270
Oh, God. More than that,
Daddy, more than that.

02:11:59.177 --> 02:12:03.341
I've felt loved,
and that's all that matters.

02:12:03.415 --> 02:12:06.942
So, never mind favorites.

02:12:07.019 --> 02:12:08.953
You're allowed to have one.

02:12:09.021 --> 02:12:12.320
The point is,
you've been mine.

02:12:15.060 --> 02:12:16.994
Oh, Allison.

02:12:18.730 --> 02:12:20.664
Oh.

02:12:24.169 --> 02:12:26.160
I really feel...

02:12:27.873 --> 02:12:30.842
I've everything I could've
ever wanted for my birthday.

02:12:30.909 --> 02:12:33.878
Oh, wait a minute!

02:12:33.946 --> 02:12:38.280
There's more to come. Lots
of excess, like you love.

02:12:40.686 --> 02:12:45.316
You know, this is gonna
be a wonderful party.

02:12:47.092 --> 02:12:49.026
Yes, it is.

02:12:52.664 --> 02:12:55.656
Thank you.
Thank you.

02:12:58.136 --> 02:13:01.594
Happy birthday!
Thanks.

02:13:26.832 --> 02:13:28.697
Thanks.
You're welcome.

02:13:28.767 --> 02:13:31.531
Good evening.
Thank you.

02:13:36.508 --> 02:13:38.533
Hello.
Welcome.

02:13:38.610 --> 02:13:41.374
<i>Hi, Susan. Hi, Simone. How are you?</i>

02:13:46.485 --> 02:13:49.943
Hi, darling.
Oh, hi, Gene. Hi.

02:14:17.049 --> 02:14:20.280
My father told me
you might be leaving.

02:14:21.353 --> 02:14:23.981
Your father and I...

02:14:24.056 --> 02:14:28.425
Our time together
has come to an end.

02:14:38.136 --> 02:14:42.004
I'm in love...
with a man,

02:14:43.408 --> 02:14:46.172
but I don't know
who he is,

02:14:46.244 --> 02:14:48.712
where he's going
or when.

02:14:51.650 --> 02:14:53.880
I can tell you
the when part.

02:14:55.320 --> 02:14:57.515
Tonight.

02:15:00.225 --> 02:15:02.819
So it does get worse.

02:15:02.894 --> 02:15:05.727
No worse
than it gets for me.

02:15:10.802 --> 02:15:13.896
I'm in love
with a woman who...

02:15:16.708 --> 02:15:21.811
I don't wanna leave.

02:15:23.582 --> 02:15:25.743
Ohh.

02:15:25.817 --> 02:15:27.842
Then don't.

02:15:31.590 --> 02:15:35.151
There's so little
we know about each other.

02:15:35.227 --> 02:15:37.457
There's so much
I should tell you.

02:15:37.529 --> 02:15:41.158
That'll come.
That'll come.

02:15:45.437 --> 02:15:48.895
Will it?
Mm-hmm.

02:15:52.177 --> 02:15:54.805
I wanna be
with you, Joe.

02:16:03.522 --> 02:16:06.491
I opened my big mouth
one too many times.

02:16:06.558 --> 02:16:09.721
Everything just got
all, uh, twisted.

02:16:09.794 --> 02:16:12.285
It's okay, Quince.
I understand.

02:16:12.364 --> 02:16:15.492
You've always meant well,
and I appreciate that.

02:16:15.567 --> 02:16:19.094
<i>Sometimes things
just turn out wrong.</i>

02:16:19.171 --> 02:16:21.105
<i>Yeah?</i>

02:16:22.941 --> 02:16:25.341
Excuse me. No, no... Uh, Joe, come in.

02:16:25.410 --> 02:16:27.935
Um, I wanna thank you.
Is it okay, Bill?

02:16:28.013 --> 02:16:31.540
- Sure.
- Joe knows the whole story. I told him.

02:16:31.616 --> 02:16:35.313
And it was his idea that
I come clean. I mean...

02:16:35.387 --> 02:16:37.787
I wanted to come clean,
but, uh,

02:16:37.856 --> 02:16:41.189
he gave me a pair of
balls, you know what I mean?

02:16:41.259 --> 02:16:43.955
Yeah,
I believe I do.

02:16:49.267 --> 02:16:51.826
Anyway, uh,

02:16:51.903 --> 02:16:54.565
I can see you guys
got business.

02:16:54.638 --> 02:16:59.235
<i>No. However, I do have some
unfinished business with Drew.</i>

02:16:59.311 --> 02:17:01.870
Get him on the helicopter.
Get him out here tonight.

02:17:01.947 --> 02:17:04.848
<i>I wanna tell this guy how I
feel about him face-to-face.</i>

02:17:04.915 --> 02:17:10.148
That could be a tall order, B.P. I doubt
if Drew is anxious to see you face-to-face.

02:17:16.193 --> 02:17:19.163
- I'll deliver the package.
- Okay.

02:17:31.376 --> 02:17:34.777
- How are you doing?
- What the hell do you care?

02:17:34.846 --> 02:17:37.610
Just asking, Bill.

02:17:40.050 --> 02:17:42.815
You wanna know?
I'll tell you.

02:17:42.887 --> 02:17:46.323
You're looking at a man who is not walking
through the valley of the shadow of death.

02:17:46.391 --> 02:17:48.985
He's galloping into it. At the
same time, the business he built...

02:17:49.059 --> 02:17:52.620
with his own hands and head has been
commandeered by a couple of cheap pirates.

02:17:52.697 --> 02:17:56.531
Oh, yes! I almost forgot. My
daughter's fallen in love with Death.

02:17:56.601 --> 02:17:59.536
And I'm in love
with your daughter.

02:18:01.606 --> 02:18:03.540
Say again?

02:18:07.679 --> 02:18:11.638
I'm in love with your daughter,
and I'm taking her with me tonight.

02:18:12.816 --> 02:18:16.308
- You what?
- I think you heard me, Bill.

02:18:16.388 --> 02:18:19.846
You're not taking Susan anywhere. What
does that mean, anyway? We had a deal.

02:18:19.924 --> 02:18:22.688
And I'm sorry.

02:18:25.063 --> 02:18:28.327
Susan's my daughter. She has
a wonderful life ahead of her.

02:18:28.400 --> 02:18:31.528
You're gonna deprive her of it,
and you're telling me you're sorry?

02:18:31.602 --> 02:18:33.867
I'm sorry.
Apology not accepted.

02:18:33.938 --> 02:18:37.669
I don't care, Bill.
I love her.

02:18:39.144 --> 02:18:41.611
How perfect for you...

02:18:41.680 --> 02:18:45.308
to take whatever you want
because it pleases you.

02:18:45.383 --> 02:18:47.681
That's not love.

02:18:47.752 --> 02:18:49.879
Then what is it?

02:18:49.954 --> 02:18:54.516
Some aimless infatuation which, for
the moment, you feel like indulging.

02:18:54.592 --> 02:18:57.152
It's missing everything
that matters.

02:18:57.227 --> 02:18:59.058
Which is what?

02:18:59.129 --> 02:19:01.791
Trust, responsibility,

02:19:01.866 --> 02:19:03.799
taking the weight for
your choices and feelings...

02:19:03.868 --> 02:19:06.462
and spending the rest of
your life living up to them,

02:19:06.538 --> 02:19:10.269
and above all, not hurting
the object of your love.

02:19:10.342 --> 02:19:12.572
So that's love according
to William Parrish?

02:19:12.644 --> 02:19:15.704
Multiply it by infinity and
take it to the depth of forever,

02:19:15.780 --> 02:19:19.442
and you will still have barely a
glimpse of what I'm talking about.

02:19:19.517 --> 02:19:23.248
Those were my words.
They're mine now.

02:19:23.321 --> 02:19:28.623
Bill, Susan wants to come
with me. She loves me.

02:19:28.692 --> 02:19:30.718
She loves you?
Mm-hmm.

02:19:30.795 --> 02:19:33.228
<i>Who is you? Did you
tell her who you are?</i>

02:19:33.298 --> 02:19:37.632
No. Does she know
where she's going? Huh?

02:19:39.404 --> 02:19:42.373
You see, Susan went for
that poor son of a bitch...

02:19:42.440 --> 02:19:45.567
whose body you took, and
everything since has been aftermath.

02:19:45.643 --> 02:19:47.611
You don't know
what love is.

02:19:47.679 --> 02:19:49.613
She doesn't know
who you are.

